      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum mechanics FEA with elastic-plastic titanium alloy material model (Ti-6Al-4V, bilinear isotropic hardening). Contact formulation captures screw-rod and screw-block interfaces. Model form justified against prior literature.",
      "rationale": "Three-dimensional continuum FEA with elastic-plastic constitutive model for Ti-6Al-4V (Young's modulus 114 GPa, yield stress 880 MPa, tangent modulus 1.1 GPa). Frictional contact (μ=0.2) at all metal-metal interfaces. Model form consistent with published spine implant simulation practice and validated in Nagaraja et al. (2023). Gradation 3 achieved. The methodology paper cited as referencesIdentifier provides additional validation context for the ensemble approach used here."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
