      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 production implants from two independent laboratories. Samples traceable to production lots; dimensional inspection records available.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested: six at Laboratory A (FDA OSEL), five at Laboratory B (DePuy Synthes). All implants from production lots with full dimensional inspection records. Inter-laboratory reproducibility assessed; coefficient of variation < 5% for stiffness across labs. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate COU loading environment. Single ASTM F1717 test configuration tested; multi-angle or multi-load-level testing not performed.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed per ASTM F1717 standard protocol at a single compression-bending angle (5°) and single load rate (5 mm/min). While environmental conditions (ambient temperature, humidity) were controlled and documented, only one test configuration was exercised. This limits confidence in model performance across the broader loading envelope relevant to in vivo use. Achieved gradation 2 is below required gradation 3; this is a noted gap acknowledged in the overall assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
